-Bootstrap query visibility now resolves through declarative module contributions rather than a central `owner_module_id` switch. Data Quality remediation dispatches nested Party mutation through the exact Party executor and verifies Party activation before the nested authoritative operation.
-
-These milestones do **not** make the architecture ready by themselves. Authoritative persisted installation lifecycle, mechanical manifest/binding/production-route parity, golden scaffolding and one unchanged all-green exact SHA remain mandatory.
+- Production mutations and queries are assembled from exact module-owned contributions; central planner, executor and query routers are absent from the production path.
+- Cross-owner reference reads occur in pre-authorization semantic validators. Data Quality nested Party remediation uses the exact Party executor and verifies Party installation state first.
+- Route and worker activation reads only durable `crm.module_installations` state. The process has no in-memory bootstrap activation bypass and does not create installation state at startup.
+- Test fixtures publish durable active installation rows when module versions are published, so production lifecycle authority and test setup remain separate concerns.
+- Background workers are discovered from a deterministic phase-ordered contribution registry and are activation-gated per tenant/module.
+- Bootstrap visibility is supplied by declarative module contributions rather than a central owner switch.
+- `production_route_parity` compares the compiled production route inventory with governed contract bindings plus exact, reasoned platform/non-runtime classifications.
+- The module scaffold creates both the infrastructure-neutral business module and a separately owned, compilable, fail-closed production composition crate.
+- Duplicate coordinates, owner mismatches, route-kind mismatches, undeclared workers and duplicate worker identities fail assembly deterministically.
+- Published module runtime identity remains immutable at the same module version.
 
 Architecture readiness is proven only when all of the following hold together on one exact commit:
 
 1. Every in-process module contributes its exact versioned mutation/query routes and background workers through the generic composition boundary.
-2. Duplicate coordinates, owner mismatches, missing handlers and route-kind mismatches fail assembly deterministically.
-3. Tenant module activation is checked before final live authorization for both mutations and queries.
-4. Cross-owner reference reads occur in pre-authorization semantic validation, never as unrelated awaited work inside the authoritative executor.
-5. Production route coverage is mechanically equal to the governed manifest/contract surface, except for explicit non-runtime classifications.
-6. Background workers are discovered from deterministic module contributions rather than fixed `ApplicationComponents` fields.
-7. Published module runtime identity is immutable at the same module version; semantic change requires a version bump.
-8. Golden scaffolding creates the production contribution boundary and its acceptance checklist.
-9. `python scripts/check_native_module_composition.py` reports no violations.
-10. All applicable workflows pass together on one unchanged exact SHA.
+2. Tenant module installation state is authoritative for routes, nested cross-module operations and workers.
+3. Manifest bindings, exact route classifications and compiled production coordinates are mechanically equal.
+4. Golden scaffolding creates the production contribution boundary and fails closed until reviewed implementation exists.
+5. `python scripts/check_native_module_composition.py` reports no violations.
+6. All applicable workflows pass together on one unchanged human-authored SHA.
 
-No marker may be suppressed or allowlisted merely to make the gate green. The corresponding legacy wiring must be removed through a real module-owned replacement.
+No marker may be suppressed or allowlisted merely to make the gate green. Any future exception must identify an exact coordinate, carry a reason and remain mechanically validated.
